Graph Separator
Overview
This program looks at connections between points (or vertices) in a graph to find out how many separate groups (or
disconnected graphs) there are. The input includes pairs of positive numbers that show which points are connected.

Features
Enter a positive number 𝑛 to indicate how many connections there are.
Input n pairs of positive numbers that represent connections in the graph.
The program will calculate and show how many separate graphs are in the input